# .trivyignore — accepted-risk CVEs for nself-admin
#
# Format: one CVE-ID per line, with a comment explaining the rationale,
# the accepted-risk owner, and the review-by date.
#
# Policy: CRITICAL CVEs must be fixed or have an explicit security team sign-off.
# HIGH CVEs are documented here with a review date not exceeding 90 days.
# Reviewers: security@nself.org
#
# --- Example (uncomment and fill in when a real CVE is accepted-risk) ---
# CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # package: <name>  severity: HIGH
#                 # rationale: not reachable from admin network surface (localhost-only)
#                 # owner: security@nself.org  review-by: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# No accepted-risk CVEs at time of S44 authoring (2026-04-20).
# All CRITICAL findings must be fixed before push.
